OK.

00:01:02.369 --> 00:01:04.368
LAUREN MAYBERRY: We're
still quite sad about it,

00:01:04.368 --> 00:01:05.180
to be honest.

00:01:05.180 --> 00:01:05.930
MALE SPEAKER: From
what I heard, it

00:01:05.930 --> 00:01:07.334
was the airport's fault, so--

00:01:07.334 --> 00:01:08.250
LAUREN MAYBERRY: Yeah.

00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:12.137
It was a catalogue of
disasters within an airport,

00:01:12.137 --> 00:01:13.970
and then there was quite
upsetting bit where

00:01:13.970 --> 00:01:15.690
me and Martin got on
the plane and could

00:01:15.690 --> 00:01:18.480
see everybody else at the gate,
but they wouldn't let them

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:20.987
on the plane even though we
could see them out the window.

00:01:20.987 --> 00:01:22.820
And then we sat on the
runway for 45 minutes

00:01:22.820 --> 00:01:24.320
while they offloaded
